  "text": "The C# type inference and method overload resolution pipeline in Roslyn is implemented across several key files in the src/Compilers/CSharp/Portable/Binder/Semantics/ directory structure:\n\n1. **OverloadResolution.cs** (src/Compilers/CSharp/Portable/Binder/Semantics/OverloadResolution/OverloadResolution.cs) - The main orchestrator class containing:\n   - OverloadResolution class: Primary controller for overload resolution\n   - Public Resolve methods: ObjectCreationOverloadResolution (line 101), MethodInvocationOverloadResolution (line 135), PropertyOverloadResolution (line 162), and MethodOrPropertyOverloadResolution (line 183)\n   - BetterFunctionMember method (overloaded at lines 1951 and 1990): Compares two method candidates to determine which is better based on parameter type conversions, following C# specification rules for implicit conversions\n   - BetterResult enum: Returns Left, Right, Neither, or Equal to indicate comparison outcomes\n   - PerformMemberOverloadResolution private method: Core resolution logic that evaluates candidates\n\n2. **MethodTypeInference.cs** (src/Compilers/CSharp/Portable/Binder/Semantics/OverloadResolution/MethodTypeInference.cs) - Handles generic type argument inference:\n   - MethodTypeInferrer struct: The main type inference engine that processes arguments against formal parameters to infer type arguments for generic methods\n   - Static Infer method (line 166): Entry point for type inference, returns MethodTypeInferenceResult with success flag and inferred type arguments\n   - MethodTypeInferenceResult struct: Contains InferredTypeArguments array, Success flag, and HasTypeArgumentInferredFromFunctionType flag\n   - InferTypeArgumentsFromFirstArgument static method (line 3072): Specialized inference for methods where types can be inferred from the first argument alone\n   - Extensions class and dependency tracking: Manages inference phases and type bounds (exact, upper, lower)\n\n3. **OverloadResolution_ArgsToParameters.cs** (src/Compilers/CSharp/Portable/Binder/Semantics/OverloadResolution/OverloadResolution_ArgsToParameters.cs) - Argument-to-parameter mapping:\n   - OverloadResolution partial class: Provides ParameterMap and argument analysis utilities\n   - ParameterMap struct: Maps argument positions to parameter positions, handling named arguments and optional parameters efficiently\n   - AnalyzeArguments and AnalyzeArgumentsForNormalFormNoNamedArguments methods: Determine applicability of arguments\n\n4. **Conversions.cs** (src/Compilers/CSharp/Portable/Binder/Semantics/Conversions/Conversions.cs) - Implicit conversion ranking:\n   - Conversions sealed class: Extends ConversionsBase to provide C#-specific conversion analysis\n   - Determines conversion classifications (identity, numeric, reference, boxing, user-defined, etc.)\n   - Used by BetterFunctionMember to rank which conversion is better when comparing two overload candidates\n   - Methods include GetMethodGroupDelegateConversion and GetMethodGroupFunctionPointerConversion for specialized conversions\n\n5. **BestTypeInferrer.cs** (src/Compilers/CSharp/Portable/Binder/Semantics/BestTypeInferrer.cs) - Best type inference for contextual typing:\n   - BestTypeInferrer static class: Handles type inference for array initializers and conditional expressions\n   - InferBestType method (line 51): Finds the best common type among a set of expressions using output type inference\n   - GetNullableAnnotation method: Merges nullable annotations using covariant joining rules\n   - GetNullableState method: Computes flow state for nullable reference types\n   - GetBestType method: Determines the best type by eliminating non-candidates through conversion checking\n\nThe pipeline flows as follows:\n1. MethodInvocationOverloadResolution receives method candidates and arguments\n2. MethodTypeInference.Infer performs generic type parameter inference for each candidate\n3. PerformMemberOverloadResolution evaluates each method's applicability\n4. BetterFunctionMember uses Conversions to compare candidates parameter-by-parameter\n5. For array/conditional contexts, BestTypeInferrer.InferBestType finds the common type\n\nThis architecture cleanly separates concerns: resolution orchestration, type inference, argument analysis, conversion ranking, and best type inference."
